====Usage notes====
"However" is not a conjunction, but a conjunctive adverb; therefore, when joining clauses with "however", a semicolon must be used and not a comma.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.une.edu.au/tlc/students/factsheets/using-however.pdf| title = Using However | format = PDF | | publisher = Academic Skills Office, [[w:University of New England, Maine|University of New England]]}}</ref>

:''I like chips; however, I detest potatoes.''

